      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHAUN LEE ROSE (8) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing sixth (24.82) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Solid record here winning nine races. Has ability and is a key runner. PAW ALLESANDRA (2) was big odds last time but gave a huge sight after a fast early split, grabbed late but holding on to a placing when a 4 length second (22.26) over 390m at Ballarat. Well-placed to take this out. TICK RETURNS (6) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by a neck at Warragul in a handy 22.93 beating Chalk And Cheese. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. One of the prime contenders. MILDRED ROSE (1) placed two back in a Grade 5 at this track then backed that up with a second (24.77) over 435m at this track last time.",
